  "prompt": "How do I submit feedback to Quora?",
  "response": "To submit feedback to Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Help Center:**\n   - Visit the Quora Help Center at [Quora Help Center](https://help.quora.com/).\n   - Browse through the help articles to see if your issue or feedback has already been addressed.\n\n2. **Contact Form:**\n   - If you need to submit particular feedback or report an issue, use the contact form.\n   - Go to the \"Contact Us\" section typically found at the bottom of Help Center articles.\n   - Fill out the form with the necessary details about your feedback or issue.\n\n3. **Using the App:**\n   - If you are using the Quora mobile app, you can usually find a \"Settings\" or \"Help\" section within the app.\n   - This section often includes options for feedback or reporting problems.\n\n4. **Email:**\n   - As of the last update, Quora does not typically list a direct email address for user feedback, preferring the above methods, but check for any updates on their site or app in case this has changed.\n\n5. **Community Forums:**\n   - Occasionally, feedback can be shared directly within community forums or discussions on Quora itself, where other users and moderators might offer assistance or forward the feedback accordingly.\n\nAlways remember to include as much detail as possible in your feedback to ensure Quora can address it effectively.",
